The residents of the Gidadawa community and its neighbours, adjacent to the Sultan of Sokoto’s Palace, Sokoto metropolis, heaved a sigh of relief yesterday, as Senator Aliyu Magatakarda Wamakko donated a 500 KVA, 11/415 KV to them. The 300 KVA transformer which was hitherto servicing the area burnt about three months ago and it had not been replaced. As a result, thousands of residents of the Gidadawa, Yar Gabas , Masunta and Nufawa communities had been thrown into total darkness since then, while all socioeconomic activities have been completely grounded due to the ugly incident. According to the engineer handling the installation of the transformer, Mr Jimoh Momoh, normal electricity supply would be fully restored to all the benefiting areas as soon as the work was completed. Momoh also said that the necessary approval is being awaited from KEDCO. Senator Aliyu Magatakarda Wamakko, who represents Sokoto North Senatorial District, explained that, his invaluable gesture was aimed at further alleviating the suffering of the residents of the benefiting communities. Senator Wamakko, who spoke through his director of Administration, Almustapha Alkali, averred that, the donation was sequel to a request made to him by a high-powered delegation from the areas, during a recent visit. He added: “afterwards, I dispatched a team of experts who assessed the situation and recommended the urgent donation of the transformer to ease the suffering of the residents.” Senator Wamakko, who is also the chairman of the Senate committee on Defence and deputy chairman, Senate committee on Anti-Corruption, urged the residents to judiciously utilise the transformer and guard it jealously from vandals. A spokesman of the residents, Alhaji Bawa Unguwar Nufawa, lauded Senator Wamakko for the unprecedented, priceless gesture.